### 📦 RASCAL Courier (Origin Prototype — Now Evolved)

The original RASCAL prototype was built for last-mile logistics. It demonstrated:

- GPS-based autonomous navigation (outdoor environments)
- Mobile-app-controlled delivery interface
- Obstacle detection and avoidance
- Mechanical robustness across terrain variation

**Prototype 1** (completed): Arduino + GPS, C++, SolidWorks-designed chassis, successful real-world delivery demo.

**Prototype 2** (in progress): Raspberry Pi, LiDAR, ROS integration, SLAM-based mapping, dynamic obstacle avoidance.

This work forms the **technical foundation** of the entire RASCAL platform. The navigation stack, sensor integration, and control systems developed for Courier are inherited by Nanny and Concierge — accelerating our build timeline significantly.

RASCAL Courier will be repositioned as a **campus and gated-community last-mile delivery product**, where autonomous delivery is viable because environments are controlled, distances are short, and labor costs are already a concern.

