## Why RASCAL Can Win in India Where Others Have Failed

| Challenge | How Others Fail | How We Win |
|---|---|---|
| Price sensitivity | B2B logistics robots compete with ₹15K/month labor | We sell to customers who pay for *emotion and status*, not labor replacement |
| Long hardware cycles | 3–5 years to product-market fit | Shared platform — Courier prototype already built; Nanny and Concierge share the stack |
| No recurring revenue | One-time hardware sales | Subscription for Nanny (cloud, AI moments); lease model for Concierge |
| Regulatory complexity | Outdoor drones/delivery face airspace rules | Indoor and campus-only deployment avoids most regulatory exposure |
| Import dependency | 90–95% of components imported | Designing for swappable commodity hardware (RPi, off-shelf sensors) from day one |

